\title{Tail #{\sigma}-field}
\taxon{definition}
\p{For a sequence #{A_1, A_2, \ldots} of events in a probability space #{(\Omega,
\mathscr{F}, P)} consider the #{\sigma}-fields #{\sigma(A_n, A_{n+1}, \ldots)}
then their intersection
##{\mathscr{T} = \bigcap_{n = 1}^{\infty} \sigma(A_n, A_{n+1}, \ldots)}
is the \em{tail #{\sigma}-field} associated with the sequence #{\{A_n\}}.
}
